metadata.title: TRAUMATIC INJURIES AND DISORDERS
metadata.definition: Nature division 1 classifies injuries resulting from traumatic force and injuries resulting from exposure to external agents and environments. These may affect one or more body system(s) or part(s) of body. Generally, a traumatic injury or disorder is the result of a single traumatic incident, event, or exposure over the course of a single shift. However, minor repetitive strain injuries that develop over a period of time, with expectation of full recovery with rest and/or minor medical care, may also be classified in this division.
metadata.includes: Effects of mechanical trauma, sharp force trauma, and acute effects of exposures and overexertions; repetitive strain injuries
metadata.excludes: Repetitive strain injuries cumulative trauma resulting in a diagnosed musculoskeletal disorder (27); prolonged exposures resulting in chronic conditions or diagnoses as disease or disorder (Division 2); Conditions or disorders that are endemic to a particular body system (Division 2)

metadata.title: Traumatic injuries or exposures-- nonspecific and unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries due to a single traumatic event or over a single shift where the nature is not specified or the full extent of the injury cannot be more precisely determined.  Symptoms that cannot be linked to a traumatic event or exposure, should be coded nature in 51.
metadata.includes: Descriptions of general “hurt ”, “trauma”, or “injury”;
metadata.excludes: Twisted joint (1440); damage to existing prosthetic or orthopedic devices (artificial limbs and eyes, hearing aids, or medical implants) without accompanying injury to the worker's body (61); unspecified injuries resulting from Event Division 7— Overexertion events (140)

metadata.title: Traumatic injuries or exposures— unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries due to a single traumatic event or exposure over a single shift where the nature is not specified and no symptoms are described.
metadata.includes: Descriptions of general “hurt ”, “trauma”, or “injury”; hip and joint replacements, or other medical procedures when the initial injury is not specified; nonfatal blunt trauma when the part is unknown; descriptions of "gave out", "could not walk", or "could not lift" without further information
metadata.excludes: Vague or nonspecific symptoms not clearly resulting from a known event or exposure occurring in a single episode (Division 5); Vague or nonspecific symptoms not clearly resulting from single traumatic event (Division 5); hypovolemic shock without further information (1230); anaphylactic shock (162); other traumatic shock (191); unspecified injuries following an overexertion incident from Event Division 7 (140)

metadata.title: Numbness, tingling
metadata.definition: Injuries that result in numbness or tingling when a more specific nature (such as allergic reaction or pinched nerve) cannot be determined.
metadata.excludes: Numbness or tingling related to underlying illness (Division 5); toxic, noxious or allergenic effects (16); traumatic injury to spinal cord (112) or peripheral nerves (149); pinched nerves (146); nerve entrapment or other known musculoskeletal issues (27)

metadata.title: Soreness, swelling, inflammation
metadata.definition: Injuries where case information gives no indication that the injury progressed beyond the symptoms of soreness, pain, inflammation, or swelling.
metadata.includes: Water on the knee with no other information; "effusion" with no other information; "jarring" injuries; "irritation" without indication of cause; cramps, spasms
metadata.excludes: Soreness and pain associated with muscle or soft tissue (14) or musculoskeletal disorders (27); "hurt" without further description (100); swelling associated with bruises (134); foreign bodies in the eye or unspecified eye irritation (1311); "irritation" resulting to exposure to toxic or allergenic substances or unspecified irritation of the skin (16); back pain, chronic or occurring after more than one shift (27); unspecified ear pain (130)

metadata.title: Nonfatal 'crushing' injuries
metadata.definition: Injuries that are described as 'crushing' where a more specific code could not be determined
metadata.includes: Crushed foot; crushed finger
metadata.excludes: crushing injuries known to involve fractures (124); crushing involving internal injuries, fatal crushing (123)

metadata.title: Other symptoms of unspecified traumatic injury or exposure— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic non-specific symptom(s) that are known but not specified elsewhere in group 100.
metadata.includes: Nausea, dizziness, upset stomach, traumatic shock when injury or exposure is unknown

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord
Injuries to the brain, spinal cord— unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries to the central nervous system, including the brain and spinal cord where a more specific code from 111 through 119 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Intracranial Injuries
metadata.definition: Injuries to the cranium or skull that involve the structures within when a more specific code from 1111 to 1119 cannot be determined. If the source document states head injuries, head trauma, closed head injuries, crushed head, blunt force trauma to the head, blunt head injury, or severe head injury, select intracranial injuries, unspecified (1110) if no other information is available.
metadata.includes: Craniocerebral trauma; traumatic brain injury or TBI; paralysis resulting from head injury; subdural hematomas; blunt force trauma to the head; blunt head injury, or severe head injury
metadata.excludes: Nonfatal skull fractures (124) — unless injury to the brain is specified (1111); neurological symptoms associated with toxic exposure (16); intracranial nerve damage, neuropathy, cerebral, hemorrhage, or strokes associated with illness (2); nondescript loss of consciousness with no apparent traumatic incident (5111)

metadata.title: Intracranial injuries— unspecified
metadata.definition: Intracranial injuries without enough information to select a more detailed code from 1111 through 1119.
metadata.includes: Craniocerebral injuries or trauma; symptoms resulting from head injuries; blunt force injuries to head
metadata.excludes: Symptoms or conditions described in 511 that are not the result of an injury or trauma; loss of consciousness without known head injury

metadata.title: Intracranial injuries with skull fractures
metadata.includes: Fatal skull fractures; skull fractures accompanied by intracranial injury; or crushing head injury

metadata.title: Cerebral and other intracranial hemorrhages without skull fracture
metadata.definition: Bleeding of the brain as a result of traumatic head injury. It is more severe than a concussion and should take precedence to be coded over a concussion.
metadata.includes: Cerebral hemorrhage; subdural hematoma; intracranial hemorrhage; subarachnoid hemorrhage; closed head injuries

metadata.title: Concussions
metadata.definition: Concussions with or without loss of consciousness and sequelae of a single incident of concussion.
metadata.includes: Concussion syndrome; post-concussive syndrome; loss of consciousness; black out from head trauma
metadata.excludes: Chronic traumatic encephalopathy (22); concussion with skull fracture (1111)

metadata.title: Other Intracranial injuries without skull fractures— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic intracranial injuries that are known and do not meet descriptions of codes 1111 through 1113.

metadata.title: Spinal cord injuries, paralysis
metadata.definition: Traumatic injuries to the spinal cord indicated by complete or partial loss of movement; reduced or altered sensation; and other loss or reduction of function.
metadata.includes: Paralysis, paraplegia, quadriplegia; severed spinal cord; incomplete spinal cord injury;  traumatic transient paralysis except due to brain injury; pinched nerves involving the spinal cord without mention of herniated or ruptured disc; fatal back fractures
metadata.excludes: Paralysis due to brain injury (111); spinal bone injury not involving nerves (124), dislocated or herniated disc (2729); back injuries not specified as involving the spinal cord

metadata.title: Spinal cord injuries, paralysis— unspecified
metadata.includes: Fatal spinal or neck fractures

metadata.title: Multiple types of injuries to the brain, spinal cord
metadata.definition: Combinations of traumatic intracranial and spinal cord injuries.
metadata.includes: Concussion and paraplegia

metadata.title: Other injuries to the brain, spinal cord— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic injury to the brain or spinal cord that is known but not listed elsewhere in group 11.
metadata.includes: Internal decapitation; atlanto-occipital dislocation
metadata.excludes: Full decapitation (1221)

metadata.title: Severe wounds, internal injuries
metadata.definition: Traumatic injuries resulting in damage to internal organs, major blood vessels and/or bones as well as injuries resulting in loss of tissue (amputations and avulsions). These may be open wounds (including gunshot wounds) or closed trauma.
metadata.includes: Gunshot wounds; trauma involving internal organs and major blood vessels; amputations, avulsions, enucleations; fractures;
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries to the brain (111) or spinal cord (112); open wounds (other than gunshot wounds) or blunt force trauma that do not specify any internal injury (13); damage to peripheral nerves (14, 27)

metadata.title: Severe wounds, internal injuries— unspecified
metadata.definition: Traumatic injuries involving major internal structures of the body, including internal organs, major blood vessels, and/or bones and injuries involving loss of tissue where a more specific code from 121-129 cannot be determined.

metadata.title: Gunshot wounds
metadata.definition: Gunshot wounds regardless of severity or location, except when a nonfatal amputation, paralysis, or nonfatal severed spine results.
metadata.includes: Grazed or pierced by bullet, bullet wound; rubber bullet wounds
metadata.excludes: Severed spine and/or paralysis resulting from gunshot wound (112); nonfatal amputations resulting from a gunshot wound (122)

metadata.title: Amputations, avulsions, enucleations
metadata.definition: Traumatic detachment or partial detachment of a limb or other external body part resulting in loss or near loss of tissue.
metadata.excludes: broken or chipped tooth (137), avulsion fracture (124); avulsion of joint capsule, ligament, or tendon in absence of tissue loss (1441)

metadata.title: Amputations, avulsions, enucleations— unspecified
metadata.definition: Traumatic detachment or partial detachment of a limb or other external body part where it is unknown if there was loss of bone.
metadata.includes: Amputation with no mention of the body part; amputations where loss of bone cannot be determined (e.g. "fingertip amputations" without further detail)

metadata.title: Amputations involving bone loss
metadata.definition: The traumatic severing or loss (either completely or partial) of a limb or other body part. This includes loss of all layers of tissue, including bone. Medical amputations resulting from irreparable damage as well as amputations of body parts that have since been reattached are considered amputations.
metadata.includes: Decapitation; injuries reported as amputations and partial amputations; traumatic injuries with bone loss; decapitations; transections; nonfatal amputations resulting from a gunshot wound; medical amputations due to irreparable traumatic injury; amputations of body parts that were surgically reattached
metadata.excludes: Fingertip "amputations" not involving bone loss (1222); internal decapitation (119); fingernail or toenail avulsions, tooth avulsions; ear avulsions, eyelid avulsion, deglovings or scalping,, enucleations, ear avulsion, severed ear,   "tearing" or "ripping" away of  part (1222); avulsion of joint capsule, ligament, muscle or tendon (1441);

metadata.title: Avulsions, enucleations without bone loss
metadata.definition: Injuries where tissue (excluding bone) has been torn or ripped away. The detachment may be partial or complete.
metadata.includes: Deglovings, scalpings, fingernail and toenail avulsions, fingertip "amputations" without bone loss, eyelid avulsions, enucleations of the eye, severed ears and noses
metadata.excludes: Detached limbs or appendages (1221); avulsion fracture (124); avulsion of joint, muscle, tendon in absence of tissue loss (1441); tooth avulsion, lost tooth (137)

metadata.title: Injuries to internal organs and major blood vessels
metadata.definition: Open wounds or closed trauma involving major internal structures of the body, including internal organs and/or major blood vessels (aorta; vena cava; pulmonary arteries and veins; brachiocephalic and subclavian arteries), neck (carotid, jugular); upper extremities (carotid, axillary, cephalic) and lower extremities (femoral, Iliac). Surface wounds or bruising related to severe trauma in this group should not be considered separate injuries. Injuries not involving injury to internal organs or blood vessels listed above should be coded in Nature group 13, "Surface and flesh wounds".
metadata.includes: Bruises, contusions, lacerations, or rupture to the internal organs and major blood vessels with or without an open wound; asphyxiation due to crushed chest or internal injuries of the trunk; arterial hematoma; traumatic rupturing of blood vessels; fatal crushing injury, or blunt force trauma to trunk; traumatic aortic aneurysm, fistula, or dissection; fatal rib fractures
metadata.excludes: Fractures without mention of injury to other structures (124); nonfatal blunt force trauma with no indication of internal injuries (10); internal injuries to the brain (111) or spinal cord (112); Injury to non-major blood vessels (listed here), bruises and contusions of exterior body, blood blisters (13);  nontraumatic aneurysm or rupture of internal organs or blood vessels (2); hemorrhagic fevers (3)

metadata.title: Injuries to internal organs, major blood vessels— unspecified
metadata.definition: Traumatic injuries without enough information to further classify the injury into any of the detailed subcategories.
metadata.includes: Blunt force trauma where open or closed wounds are unspecified; Injuries resulting in hypovolemia without further information; traumatic collapsed lung without further information;
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries to the brain (111) or spinal cord (112); Injuries to peripheral nerves (14)

metadata.title: Open wounds involving internal organs, major blood vessels
metadata.definition: Injuries that are the result of lacerating or puncturing the body surface and result in injuries to internal organs and/or major blood vessels
metadata.includes: Lacerations, punctures, stab wounds or impaling wounds that injure internal organs and/or major blood vessels; injuries causing exsanguination
metadata.excludes: Open head injuries (1111); gunshot wounds (121); amputations, enucleations (122); surface wounds or bruises (13); animal or insect bites; needlesticks (13); ruptured eardrum (136); cuts or lacerations that do not involve internal organs and structures (132)

metadata.title: Closed trauma involving internal organs, major blood vessels
metadata.definition: Closed trauma resulting in injuries to internal organs and major blood vessels
metadata.includes: Rib fractures with internal chest injuries; ruptured blood vessel; fatal "crushing" injuries; "crushing" injuries with internal damage; fractures and internal injuries
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries to the brain (111) or spinal cord (112); Injuries to peripheral nerves (14); fatal blunt force injuries to head (1110)

metadata.title: Multiple open and closed wounds involving internal organs, major blood vessels
metadata.definition: Injuries that are the result of a combination of types of trauma, including blunt, sharp force, and/or overexertion and result in injuries to internal organs, major nerves or major blood vessels.

metadata.title: Injuries to internal organs, major blood vessels— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic internal injuries that are specified, but do not meet definitions of codes 1231-1238.

metadata.title: Fractures
metadata.definition: Fractures (i.e. breaks or chips) of bones. Nose and rib fractures are assumed to be bone fractures unless otherwise specified.  Bruising and damage to surrounding tissue associated with the fracture should not be considered a separate injury.
metadata.includes: Closed fractures; open fractures; comminuted, compound, depressed, elevated, fissured, greenstick, impacted, linear, march, simple, stress and spiral fractures; slipped epiphysis; broken or cracked bones;  fractures resulting from nonvenomous animal bites; avulsion fractures; joint fractures
metadata.excludes: Fatal fractures of the skull (1111); fractures that involve damage to spinal cord (112); rib fractures involving damage to internal organs(123); tooth avulsion (137);  fracture of cartilage (14); avulsions of joint capsule, ligament, or tendon (1441); dislocations and fractures (1824); pathological or spontaneous fracture (279);  dental injuries, broken or chipped tooth (137);

metadata.title: Multiple severe wounds and internal injuries
metadata.definition: Multiple types of severe wounds and trauma affecting internal structures, select this subgroup when more than one type of severe wound or trauma is specified.

metadata.title: Severe wounds, internal injuries— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Injuries affecting internal structures that are known but do not meet descriptions of codes in groups 121 through 128.
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries to the brain (111) or spinal cord (112); Injuries to peripheral nerves (14)

metadata.title: Surface and flesh wounds
metadata.definition: Wounds and trauma that do not involve internal organs, bones or major blood vessels. This group also includes injuries that are specific to eyes, ears, and teeth. Assume no injury to internal structures if none is stated.
metadata.excludes: Injuries affecting internal organs or major blood vessels of the trunk (aorta; vena cava; pulmonary arteries and veins; brachiocephalic and subclavian arteries); neck (carotid, jugular); upper extremities (carotid, axillary, cephalic) and lower extremities (femoral, Iliac) (12); surface damage accompanied by more serious wounds

metadata.title: Surface and flesh wounds— unspecified
metadata.definition: Wounds and trauma that do not involve internal organs, bones or major blood vessels when there is not enough information to select a more detailed code from 131 through 139.
metadata.includes: "Jammed" finger(s) or toe(s) without other information; bloody nose with no other information; a "bump" on body after contact without further information; "hurt" eye; ear pain following traumatic event

metadata.title: Injuries specific to eyes
metadata.definition: Injuries that are specific to the eyes. Other types of eye injuries such as bruising or laceration should be coded with the general codes for those natures.
metadata.excludes: Unspecified injuries to the eye (100); enucleation of eye (1222); sensory disturbances due to intracranial injuries (111); bruising around eye, 'black eye' (134); puncture of the eye (132)

metadata.title: Eye abrasion(s), irritation— except chemical or allergic
metadata.definition: Abrasions of the cornea and conjunctiva or other swelling and irritation caused by item striking eye or foreign object or substance in eye except when chemical or allergic irritation is not specified or when abrasion is noted.
metadata.includes: Abrasions of the cornea(s), lens(es), conjunctiva; foreign object or substance in eye without specific injury; eye irritation, except chemical or allergic; redness and swelling of eye(s) due to trauma
metadata.excludes: Bruising around eye, 'black eye'; chemical burns to eye (15); chemical or allergic irritation of eye (16)

metadata.title: Retinal tear
metadata.definition: A separation of the retina from its connection at the back of the eye which often occurs when the vitreous gel pulls loose or separates from its attachment to the retina.
metadata.includes: Retina detachment
metadata.excludes: Conjunctivitis, chemical (16); conjunctivitis, bacterial or viral (Division 2)

metadata.title: Cuts, lacerations, punctures without injury to internal structures
metadata.definition: Open wounds that do not affect bones, internal organs or listed major blood vessels. For lacerations where it is unknown if internal structures were affected, select this code. (See Nature 123 description for list of blood major vessels)
metadata.includes: Gashes; slices; prick; splinters; slivers; scratches; needlestick injuries without disease exposure or exposure unknown; mosquito bite and other minor nonvenomous insect bites; animal bites not affecting internal structures
metadata.excludes: Venomous animal or insect bites or stings (16); bites or stings that simultaneously produce a parasitic or infectious disease (Division 3)

metadata.title: Abrasions
metadata.definition: Injuries where the skin, mucous membrane, or superficial epithelium have been removed or marked, usually as a result of rubbing or scraping.
metadata.includes: Scraped; skinned; friction burns; road rash; chaffing
metadata.excludes: Injuries involving extensive loss of skin that is exposing underlying tissue are considered avulsions (1222); minor scratches and abrasions that simultaneously transmit MRSA (2813) or other cellulitis (2311)

metadata.title: Bruises, contusions
metadata.definition: Injuries that produce capillary hemorrhaging with the skin remaining intact. Bruises involving hemorrhage from broken bones, internal organs, major blood vessels and nerves are coded in 12. Assume no injury to internal structures if none is stated.
metadata.includes: Bruises and contusions—with or without swelling; hematoma (except brain); black eye; ecchymosis; hyphemia; contusions resulting from nonvenomous animal bites; bruised bones; "knot" or "bump" following trauma; non-fatal "crushing" injuries that do not mention fractures or internal injuries; DVT resulting from bruise, contusion
metadata.excludes: Swelling without other information (102); concussion or other traumatic injuries to the brain (1113); injuries to the internal organs of the trunk (123); traumatic hemarthrosis (1440);  nontraumatic cerebral hemorrhage (2360)

metadata.title: Blisters
metadata.includes: Blood blisters; friction blisters
metadata.excludes: Blistering from burns (15), corrosions (15), or toxic/allergenic reactions (16); blisters associated with other diseases, disorders, or injuries (Division 2, 3, etc.)

metadata.title: Ruptured eardrum
metadata.definition: A rupture or perforation of the eardrum.
metadata.includes: Perforations due to trauma, explosions, pressure, or loud noise; punctured eardrum
metadata.excludes: Hearing loss or damage; tinnitus, ringing in ears (2262); perforation caused by otitis media (infection)

metadata.title: Dental injuries
metadata.definition: Injuries to teeth or gums
metadata.includes: chipped or broken tooth; lost tooth, tooth avulsion; loose tooth

metadata.title: Multiple surface and flesh wounds
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries and disorders of equal severity within major group 13.
metadata.includes: Abrasions and bruises of equal severity

metadata.title: Surface and flesh wounds— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Wounds and trauma involving skin, muscle, connective tissues but excluding bones, internal organs, or listed major blood vessels that are known but do not meet descriptions of codes 131 through 138.
metadata.includes: Foreign object in natural orifice (e.g. item lodged in ear canal or nasal passages); vocal injury or strain
metadata.excludes: Venomous animal or insect bites or stings (16), bites or stings that simultaneously produce a parasitic or infectious disease (Division 3)

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries
metadata.definition: Codes in this group describe injuries involving soft tissues (i.e. muscles, tendons, ligaments, cartilage, joints and peripheral nerves). These types of Injuries may result from acute disruption of tissues from a single incident of trauma, such as a car accident. It also includes injuries from incidents involving single episode strains and overexertions or minor repetitive strain that does not result in a disorder or disease in from Nature Group 27 - Musculoskeletal disorders.
metadata.includes: Avulsions of joint capsule, ligament, or tendon; dislocations or internal derangement, shoulder separations; torn or fractured cartilage; sprains, strains, tears;  hernias, except congenital or disease-related; whiplash
metadata.excludes: Spinal cord injuries (112); gunshot wounds (121); avulsions involving open wounds with tissue loss (1233); joint fractures and avulsion fractures (124); hernias resulting from congenital defect or disease  (259)

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries— unspecified
metadata.definition: Symptoms resulting after musculoskeletal injury or overexertion. Traumatic and minor repetitive strain injuries of the musculoskeletal system without enough information to select a detailed code from 141 through 149.
metadata.includes: Joint popping with no other information; back spasms, muscle spasms (except toxic effects 16 or environmental conditions 17); muscle pain, soreness, hurt after musculoskeletal trauma or overexertion
metadata.excludes: Pain or soreness resulting from a repetitive overexertion or cumulative trauma (270)

metadata.title: Dislocations
metadata.definition: Displacement or dislocation of bone or cartilage with or without cartilage tears.
metadata.includes: Subluxations or partial dislocations; joint hyperextension; shoulder separations or dislocations; dislocated knee, traumatic internal derangement
metadata.excludes: Cartilage tears without dislocation (143); herniated and dislocated discs (2729); dislocations and fractures (1824)

metadata.title: Hernias
metadata.definition: Injuries resulting in part of an organ becoming displaced and protruding through the wall of the cavity containing it. This code includes hernias resulting from single or repetitive exertion or trauma, and hernias of undetermined cause.
metadata.includes: Ruptured and strangulated hernias from a single or unknown period of exertion
metadata.excludes: Strangulated hernia, hernias resulting from congenital defect or disease (259); herniated brain (2239);  bladder prolapse (269); synovial and Birkett's hernia (2755); herniated disc (27)

metadata.title: Cartilage fractures and tears
metadata.definition: Tears and fractures to cartilage, and major tears to muscles, tendons, and ligaments.
metadata.includes: Meniscus and labral tears
metadata.excludes: Nose and rib fractures are coded as bone fractures unless specifically described as being limited to cartilage (124); dislocations involving cartilage tears (141)

metadata.title: Cartilage fractures and tears— unspecified
metadata.definition: Traumatic injury to cartilage where injuries are described without enough information to further classify the injury into any of the detailed subcategories.
metadata.includes: Cartilage tear with no body part mentioned

metadata.title: Meniscus tear
metadata.definition: Tear to the meniscus cartilage of the knee.
metadata.includes: Medial meniscus; lateral meniscus
metadata.excludes: ACL or MCL tear, tears to ligaments, muscles or tendons (144)

metadata.title: Other cartilage fractures and tears— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic injury to cartilage other than meniscus tears.
metadata.includes: Fractured cartilage of the nose, unless a bone was also fractured; torn or fractured meniscus or labrum of the shoulder or hip; glenoid labrum tear or lesion, or SLAP tear
metadata.excludes: Torn meniscus of the knee (1431)

metadata.title: Sprains, strains, tears
metadata.definition: Sprains, strains and tears of muscles, tendons, and ligaments. Sprains, strains, and tears are assumed to be minor (grade I or II) unless otherwise specified.  Sprains are the stretching or tearing of ligaments, while strains are similar injuries involving muscles and tendons.  Diseases or disorders affecting the musculoskeletal system, including tendonitis and bursitis, which generally occur over time as a result of repetitive activity should be coded in Musculoskeletal system and connective tissue diseases and disorders, Group 27.
metadata.includes: Traumatic hemarthrosis or bleeding in the knee joint (1440);  rotator cuff strains; "pull", rupture, strain, sprain, or minor tear of joint capsule, ligament, muscle, or tendon; unspecified "twists" of joints
metadata.excludes: Lacerations of tendons in open wounds (13); cartilage tears (143); meniscus tears (1431); hernias (142); injuries due to repetitive activity (27);

metadata.title: Sprains, strains, tears— unspecified
metadata.definition: Sprains, strains and tears of muscles, tendons, and ligaments when there is not sufficient description to select a detailed code from 1441 through 1448
metadata.includes: Descriptions of "felt a pull" with no other information;  descriptions of muscle spasms associated with an overexertion event

metadata.title: Major tears to muscles, tendons, ligaments
metadata.definition: Tears that are described as grade III or assumed to be major-ACL, MCL, rotator cuff, Achilles, and biceps tears. "Ruptures" to muscles, tendons and ligaments
metadata.includes: Anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) tear; medial collateral ligament tear (MCL); Achilles tear or rupture; torn rotator cuff; bicep(s) tear; grade III sprain or strain; avulsion of joint capsule, ligament, or tendon that does not involve open wound with tissue loss; rotator cuff tears or avulsions of joint capsule, ligament, or tendon that do not involve open wounds; "Ruptures" to muscles, tendons and ligaments
metadata.excludes: Meniscus tears (1431); grade I and II sprains and strains (1442); rotator cuff syndrome; (2759); nontraumatic rotator cuff tendinitis (2755)

metadata.title: Sprains, strains, minor tears
metadata.includes: Rolled ankle; twisted ankle; pulled muscle

metadata.title: Multiple major and minor sprains, strains, tears
metadata.definition: Combinations of major tears (1441) with sprains and strains and/or minor tears (1442).
metadata.includes: Rotator cuff tear with a sprained back

metadata.title: Whiplash
metadata.definition: Injuries that may involve damage to both the bone structures and soft tissues of the neck, where 'whiplash' is specified in the source documents.
metadata.includes: Whiplash with no mention of other specific injury

metadata.title: Pinched nerve
metadata.definition: Traumatic injuries to nerves resulting from a single episode of trauma or repetitive strain over one work shift or less.
metadata.excludes: Spinal cord injury (112); nerve damage due to chemical or environmental exposure (16 or 17); Other musculoskeletal nerve impingement or entrapment, except the back (274); carpal tunnel, tarsal tunnel (27*)

metadata.title: Multiple soft tissue injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of two or more different injuries from the 14 codes.
metadata.includes: Sprain and whiplash

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic and minor repetitive strain injuries of the musculoskeletal system that are known, but do not meet descriptions of codes 141 through 148.
metadata.includes: Injuries to peripheral nerves occurring in one shift; capsulitis
metadata.excludes: Soft tissue and musculoskeletal disorders developing over more than one shift (27)

metadata.title: Burns, corrosions, electrical injuries
metadata.definition: Burns (tissue damage) resulting from a variety of sources including heat, flame, hot substance, lightning, radiation, extremely cold objects, and electricity. It also includes the corrosive action of chemicals, chemical compounds and fumes including acids and caustics. When there are multiple burns or corrosions of differing degree, code the most severe. Use the appropriate unspecified code for all burns (chemical, heat, scalds, electrical) when the degree cannot be determined. First degree burns or epidural burns are the least severe and are characterized by pain and reddening of the skin. Second degree burns are more severe and characterized by blistering, swelling and destruction of superficial tissue. Partial thickness burns that involve the superficial dermis are considered second-degree burns. Third and fourth degree burns are the most severe. They may be described as partial thickness—deep or full thickness.
metadata.includes: Chemical burns; heat, thermal and scalding burns, internal burns from inhaling hot smoke and gases; electrical and lightning burns, burns from arc flashes; first, second, and third degree burns; radiation burns; ultraviolet keratoconjunctivitis, sunburns, and welder’s flash—first degree or degree unspecified
metadata.excludes: Frostbite (1711); burns and smoke inhalation (1851), fractures and burns (1826); traumatic sensory loss and burns, 3rd degree or higher (18); effects other than burns from chemicals (16); eye injuries resulting from lasers

metadata.title: Burns, corrosions, electrical injuries— unspecified
metadata.definition: Burns (tissue damage) where injuries are described without enough information to determine the type of burn in detailed codes 151 through 159.
metadata.includes: burn with no mention of type or cause

metadata.title: Chemical burns, corrosions
metadata.definition: Burns and wounds that result from the corrosive action of chemicals, the corrosive action of chemicals, chemical compounds, and fumes including acids and caustics. Unless noted as burns, skin exposures where blistering or multi-layer tissue damage is not specified should be coded as nature 167, contact irritant dermatitis.
metadata.includes: Chemical burns to eye(s)
metadata.excludes: Chemical conjunctivitis, contact irritant dermatitis (167);

metadata.title: Chemical burns, corrosions— degree unspecified
metadata.definition: Burns (tissue damage) where injuries are described without enough information to determine the degree of severity.
metadata.includes: Burns due to chemicals, acids, powders, solutions, cleaners (with no mention of heat), bleach, stripper, freon, caustic substances, etc.
metadata.excludes: Contact dermatitis (167)

metadata.title: Chemical burns, corrosions— third degree or higher
Thermal burns
metadata.definition: Burns that result from contact with fire or hot objects. It excludes burns caused by exposure to electricity.
metadata.includes: Burns due to fire, flame, steam, hot coffee, burning, boiling, or molten substances, fryers, sparks, torches, etc.
metadata.excludes: Thermal burns accompanied by electric shock (174);  burns from arc flashes or lightning; burns from electric shock (153); burns from radiating heat, sunburn (159)

metadata.title: Thermal burns— degree unspecified
metadata.definition: Thermal burns without enough information to determine the degree of severity.

metadata.title: Thermal burns— second degree
metadata.includes: Partial thickness burns

metadata.title: Thermal burns— third degree or higher
Effects of electric current
metadata.definition: Fatal and nonfatal traumatic injuries that result from contact with electric current.
metadata.includes: electric shock; lightning strike; electric burns; combinations of injuries from electric current exposure; burns from arc flashes and other contact with electric current

metadata.title: Effects of electric current— unspecified
metadata.definition: Fatal and nonfatal traumatic injuries that result from contact with electric current where a more specific code from 1531 to 1538 could not be determined.

metadata.title: Electrical burns— any degree
metadata.includes: Arc burns; clothing melting to skin; thermal contact burns

metadata.title: Electrocution, electric shock
metadata.definition: Fatal and nonfatal injuries resulting from electricity passing through the body.
metadata.includes: Internal organ damage; internal burns; neurological injuries; cardiac effects; electrocution or electric shock without mention of burns

metadata.title: Electrical burns and electrocution
metadata.definition: Internal and external electrical injuries

metadata.title: Other or multiple types of burns
metadata.definition: Combinations of burns in group 15 or types of burns known not listed in group 15.
metadata.includes: Radiation burns; friction burns; sunburn
metadata.excludes: Cold burns, frostbite (1711); road rash (133)

metadata.title: Other or multiple types of burns— degree unspecified
metadata.definition: Other or multiples types of burns described without enough information to determine the degree of severity.
metadata.includes: Chemical and heat burns

metadata.title: Other or multiple types of burns— first degree
metadata.includes: Ultraviolet keratoconjunctivitis; welder's flash; flash burns; friction burns, and sunburn when the degree of burn is unspecified.
metadata.excludes: Traumatic sensory loss, blindness (114)

metadata.title: Other or multiple types of burns— second degree
Other or multiple types of burn— third degree or higher
Effects of poison, toxic, or allergenic exposure
metadata.definition: Poisoning or toxic, noxious, or allergenic effects resulting from short-term exposures to chemicals, venoms, drugs, medicines, food, and other substances.
metadata.includes: Systemic or body system reactions as a result of exposure to toxins, allergens or poisons; allergic or toxic reactions limited to the skin, eyes, or mucosa

metadata.title: Effects of poison, toxic, or allergenic exposure— unspecified
metadata.definition: Poisoning or toxic, noxious, or allergenic effects where injuries are described without enough information to further classify the injury into any of the detailed subcategories.
metadata.includes: Unspecified reactions to venomous bites and stings not limited to the skin

metadata.title: Poisoning, poisoning-related asphyxia
metadata.definition: Death or injury or harm to organs, as a result from exposure to poisonous substance(s) usually by chemical reactions or other activity on a molecular scale, when an organism absorbs a sufficient quantity.
metadata.includes: Drug overdoses and smoke inhalations when no specific information is available; passing out due to chemical exposure, fumes or gas; carbon monoxide poisoning; toxic effects of food contaminants or noxious food stuffs—non-viral and non-bacterial; lead poisoning; radiation sickness or poisoning
metadata.excludes: Anaphylactic shock, anaphylaxis

metadata.title: Anaphylactic shock, anaphylaxis
metadata.definition: Inflammatory response in one or more body systems as a result of extreme allergic reaction. It may result in inability to breathe. This code should be used if the source documents specify anaphylactic shock or anaphylaxis
metadata.includes: Anaphylactic reactions to insect bites or stings; food allergies

metadata.title: Poison, toxic, or allergenic effects— other respiratory
metadata.definition: Toxic or allergenic effects not listed above that are limited (localized) to the respiratory system.
metadata.includes: Wheezing; shortness of breath; tightening of chest; lung irritation;  coughing, throat irritation; asthma attacks or exacerbation from short-term exposures to toxic or allergenic substances; reactive airway disease; allergic rhinitis
metadata.excludes: Anaphylaxis (162); asthma attack with no apparent cause or exercise induced asthma (2433); poisoning-related asphyxia (161)

metadata.title: Poison, toxic, or allergenic effects—dizziness, headache
metadata.includes: Lightheadedness; fainting
metadata.excludes: Dizziness, lightheadedness, headache with no toxic exposure or due to trauma or illness

metadata.title: Poison, toxic, or allergenic effects—nausea, vomiting
metadata.excludes: Nausea, vomiting due to trauma with no toxic exposure or due to trauma or illness

metadata.title: Urticaria, hives— acute
metadata.definition: Raised, itchy areas of skin that are usually a sign of an allergic reaction. These may appear beyond just the site of the exposure indicating a systemic body response.
metadata.includes: Dermatitis resulting from inhaling or ingesting substances; hives
metadata.excludes: Contact dermatitis and occupational dermatitis, poison ivy, oak, or sumac (167); rash due to underlying disease

metadata.title: Allergic and irritant dermatitis— acute
metadata.definition: Localized (limited to site of exposure) reactions or injuries of the skin and mucosa that are the result of exposure to harmful or allergenic substances.
metadata.includes: Contact dermatitis due to metals, adhesives, rubber, latex, animals, or food; contact and occupational dermatitis; poison ivy, oak, or sumac; Rhus; venomous bug bites and stings limited to the skin without systemic reaction; irritating or allergenic substance in eye(s)
metadata.excludes: Chemical burns, chemical exposure resulting in blistering or multi-layer tissue damage (151); unspecified reaction to venomous bites and stings (160); hives or systemic reactions of the skin that spread to more than area of contact (166); dermatitis caused by parasites or from long term exposures (282); eczema not specified as acute (282); lice (391); scabies, chiggers, and mites (392); cellulitis (2811); heat rash and prickly heat (2893); dermatoses, neurodermatitis, perioral dermatitis, pruritis (2899);

metadata.title: Multiple effects of poison, toxic, or allergenic exposure
metadata.definition: Combinations of two or more different reactions from group 16.
metadata.includes: Combination of systemic reactions; combination of systemic and skin reactions

metadata.title: Effects of poison, toxic, or allergenic exposure— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Poisoning or toxic, noxious, or allergenic effects

metadata.title: Effects of environmental conditions and exposures
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders that are a result of adverse environmental conditions or exposures.
metadata.includes: Effects of temperature, light, air and water pressure; dehydration resulting from environmental conditions
metadata.excludes: Other burns (15); sunburn (1591)

metadata.title: Effects of environmental conditions and exposures— unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders that are a result of adverse environmental conditions or exposures without enough information to further classify the injury into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Effects of reduced temperature
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders resulting from abnormally reduced body temperature which affects body tissues, or the functioning of the central nervous system, circulatory system, or the endocrine system.

metadata.title: Effects of reduced temperature— unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders resulting from abnormally reduced body temperature

metadata.title: Frostbite
metadata.includes: Burns from extremely cold objects, cold burns

metadata.title: Hypothermia
metadata.excludes: drowning, with hypothermia (174)

metadata.title: Multiple effects of reduced temperature
metadata.definition: Combinations of two or more different effects from subgroup 171.

metadata.title: Effects of reduced temperature— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders resulting from abnormally reduced body temperature that are known but not listed in subgroup 171.
metadata.includes: Trench foot, chilblains, erythema pernio, perniosis

metadata.title: Effects of heat and light
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders caused by the effects of heat and light.
metadata.includes: Heat stroke, heat apoplexy, heat pyrexia, ictus solaris, siriasis, sunstroke, thermoplegia, fatal hyperthermia; heat exhaustion, fainting and loss of consciousness associated with heat, heat fatigue including transient;  dehydration resulting from heat exposure
metadata.excludes: Fainting and loss of consciousness without reference to heat (5111) or trauma (1110); sunburn—first degree or degree unspecified (1591); heat burns (152); prickly heat, heat rash, miliaria rubra (2893)

metadata.title: Effects of heat— unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders caused by the effects of heat and light where injuries are described without enough information to further classify the injury into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Heat stroke, syncope
metadata.definition: Includes elevation of core body temperature and/or loss of consciousness. May include effects of dehydration.
metadata.includes: Documented elevation of core body temperature and/or loss of consciousness or fainting
metadata.excludes: Dehydration not related to heat exposure (179)

metadata.title: Heat exhaustion, fatigue
metadata.definition: Includes exhaustion, fatigue, or other symptoms related to heat exposure in the absence of elevated body temperature or loss of consciousness. May include effects of dehydration.
metadata.includes: Prostration, nausea, vomiting, muscle weakness, heat cramps, headache without loss of consciousness
metadata.excludes: Dehydration not related to heat exposure (179)

metadata.title: Effects of heat— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders caused by the effects of heat and light that are known but not listed in subgroup 172.
metadata.includes: Heat edema; Heat-related dehydration
metadata.excludes: Dehydration not related to heat exposure (179)

metadata.title: Effects of air or water pressure
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders resulting from effects of high and low air or water pressure or changes in air or water pressure.
metadata.includes: Barotitis, otitic barotrauma, sinus barotrauma, barosinusitis, ruptured eardrum due to air or water pressure, air or gas embolisms due to diving, decompression sickness or illness, effects of high altitude, effects of underwater pressure changes
metadata.excludes: Injuries resulting from blasts of pressurized air or water (62) ruptured eardrum due to air or water pressure (136)

metadata.title: Effects of air or water pressure— unspecified
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders resulting from effects of high and low air or water pressure or changes in air or water pressure where injuries are described without enough information to further classify the injury into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Aero-otitis media
metadata.definition: Traumatic inflammation of the middle ear resulting from differences in atmospheric pressure.
metadata.includes: Otitic barotrauma; barotitis

metadata.title: Aero sinusitis
metadata.definition: Inflammation of the paranasal sinus cavities caused by air pressure differences.
metadata.includes: Sinusitis barotrauma: sinus barotrauma

metadata.title: Caisson disease, bends, divers' palsy
metadata.definition: Air or gas embolisms due to diving.
metadata.includes: Paralysis, convulsions, difficulties with muscle coordination, and sensory abnormalities due to bubbles in the body; decompression sickness

metadata.title: Multiple effects of air or water pressure
metadata.definition: Combinations of two or more different effects from subgroup 173.

metadata.title: Effects of air or water pressure— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Injuries or disorders resulting from effects of high and low air or water pressure or changes in air or water pressure that are known but not listed in subgroup 173.

metadata.title: Drowning, near drowning
metadata.definition: The process of experiencing respiratory impairment from submersion or immersion in liquid, especially in water. Drownings may be fatal or non-fatal.
metadata.includes: drowning with hypothermia

metadata.title: Asphyxiation— except toxic or allergenic
metadata.definition: Fatal and nonfatal injuries that involve the lack of oxygen, stopping of the respiration process, or obstruction to breathing not caused by poisoning, toxic or allergenic exposure.
metadata.includes: Traumatic, mechanical, positional, and compressional asphyxia—except when crushing or internal injuries of the trunk are specified; asphyxia resulting from an oxygen-deficient environment except where gas fumes or vapors are involved; asphyxiation by constriction, hanging, strangulation, or suffocation; inhaling or choking on food or other substances engulfment in materials such as grain
metadata.excludes: Asphyxiation due to crushed chest or internal injuries of the trunk (123); poisoning, toxic or allergenic exposure (16); asphyxia from exposure to fumes or vapors, smoke inhalation, carbon monoxide poisoning (161); drowning (174); strangulated hernia (259)

metadata.title: Multiple effects of environmental conditions and exposures
metadata.definition: Combinations of two or more different effects from group 17 not classified by a more specific code in group 17.

metadata.title: Other effects of environmental conditions and exposures— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Effects that are known but not listed in group 17 and not classified by a more specific code in group 17.
metadata.includes: Effects of dehydration, except heat related; exhaustion, except heat related

metadata.title: Multiple traumatic injuries and disorders
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity, or where relative severity is unknown. When two or more injuries are present in a case and relative severity cannot be determined, look for a combination code BEFORE attempting to use the severity guide in Nature rule of selection 2.c.iv. If other injuries are not specified, code to only the specified nature. For example, if source documents state "intracranial injuries and other injuries", select Nature code 1110, Intracranial injuries, unspecified.

metadata.title: Multiple traumatic injuries and disorders— unspecified
metadata.excludes: Excludes injuries to named parts or any specific injuries

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord and other injuries
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries to the brain, spinal cord and other unspecified injuries (11).

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord and severe wounds, internal injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 11 and 12
metadata.includes: Blunt force trauma to the head and trunk; intracranial injuries and fractures (other than skull); intracranial injuries and amputations

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord and soft tissue injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 11 and 14
metadata.includes: concussions and whiplash

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord and burns
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 11 and 15

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord and toxic, allergenic effects
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 11 and 16
metadata.includes: Concussions and poisoning related asphyxia

metadata.title: Injuries to the brain, spinal cord and effects of environmental exposure
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity involving codes from group 11 and 17
metadata.includes: Intracranial injuries and electrocution

metadata.title: Severe wounds or internal injuries and other injuries
metadata.excludes: Severe wounds affecting internal organs and structures and other unspecified injuries (12).

metadata.title: Severe wounds or internal injuries and soft tissue injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 14
metadata.includes: Blunt or sharp force internal injuries with severe dislocation(s), tear(s), or strain(s)

metadata.title: Severe wounds, internal injuries and burns
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 15

metadata.title: Fractures and surface, flesh wounds
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 13
metadata.includes: Fractures and road rash; fractures and lacerations

metadata.title: Fractures and soft tissue injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 14
metadata.includes: Fractures and dislocations; fractures and tears

metadata.title: Fractures and burns
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 15

metadata.title: Severe wounds, internal injuries and toxic, allergenic effects
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 16
metadata.includes: Loss of consciousness from toxic fumes and internal injuries (e.g. from fall)

metadata.title: Severe wounds, internal injuries and electrocution, electric shock
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 12 and 1532
metadata.includes: electric shock and internal injuries (e.g. from fall)
metadata.excludes: Internal injuries resulting from electrocution (153)

metadata.title: Surface and flesh wounds and other injuries
metadata.excludes: Wounds and trauma (not involving internal organs and structures) and other unspecified injuries (13).

metadata.title: Surface, flesh wounds and soft tissue injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 13 and 14
metadata.includes: Cuts and sprains or strains; bruises and muscle tears

metadata.title: Surface, flesh wounds and toxic, allergenic effects
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 13 and 16
metadata.includes: Cuts and smoke inhalation

metadata.title: Surface, flesh wounds and burns, electrical injuries
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 13 and 15
metadata.includes: Bruises and electrocution; burns and lacerations

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries and other injuries
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries of the musculoskeletal system and other unspecified injuries (14)

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries and burns
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 14 and 15
metadata.includes: Sprain and burn

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries and toxic, allergenic effects
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 14 and 16

metadata.title: Soft tissue injuries and effects of electrical current
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 14 and 153

metadata.title: Burns and toxic effects (including smoke inhalation)
metadata.definition: Combinations of injuries of equal or similar severity from groups 15 and 16
metadata.includes: Burns and smoke inhalation
metadata.excludes: Burns and other unspecified injuries (15); electric burns and electric shock (1538)

metadata.title: Traumatic injuries— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Traumatic injuries that are not classified in any of the above groups. It includes injuries of the sensory organs as well as other types of injuries or disorders that are known but do not match descriptions of codes in groups 10 through 18.

metadata.title: Traumatic shock
metadata.definition: A physiological response to physical or emotional trauma characterized by a variety of symptoms including drop in blood pressure, nausea, anxiety or panic, dissociation, nonresponsiveness or unconsciousness. Select this code if injured worker displays these symptoms in the absence of another physical injury following a traumatic event.
metadata.includes: Any of the following symptoms after a traumatic event in the absence of injuries due to mechanical trauma or exposure to harmful substance: anxiety; panic attack; confusion; nonresponsiveness; nausea
metadata.excludes: Hypervolemic shock (123); Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (long term diagnosis) (Division 6)

metadata.title: Other traumatic injuries— n.e.c.
metadata.includes: stitches rupturing; embolism, air or fat-- except due to diving, elevation exposure
metadata.excludes: Foreign object or substance in eye without specific injury (131); foreign object in nature orifice (139); divers' palsy, bends, caisson disease (1733)

metadata.title: DISEASES AND DISORDERS OF BODY SYSTEMS
metadata.definition: Nature division 2 classifies diseases or disorders affecting systems of the body. Diseases or disorders included may affect the whole named body system, or more commonly, affect only a part of the named body systems at the time of diagnosis.  This conditions may be toxic or non-toxic and include advanced effects of single or repetitive exposure or exertion.
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries and disorders (Division 1); infectious and parasitic diseases (Division 3); neoplasms, tumors, and cancers (Division 4)

metadata.title: Systemic diseases and disorders— unspecified
metadata.definition: Nature code 20 classifies instances where diseases or disorders are described without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Anemia and other diseases of the blood and blood forming organs
metadata.definition: Toxic and non-toxic diseases of the blood and blood forming organs.
metadata.includes: Anemias; coagulation defects; purpura and other hemorrhagic conditions; aplasia; agranulocytosis and neutropenia; sickle-cell anemia; thalassemia; thrombocytasthenia; thrombasthenia; qualitative platelet defects; polycythemia; pancytopenia; diseases of white blood cells; toxic paralytic anemia; Evans syndrome; thrombocytopenia
metadata.excludes: Leukemia (4134)

metadata.title: Nervous system and sense organs diseases
metadata.definition: Inflammatory, degenerative, and other disorders of the central and peripheral nervous system. Disorders of the sense organs of sight and hearing are also included in this group.
metadata.includes: Disorders of the sense organs of sight and hearing.

metadata.title: Nervous system and sense organs diseases— unspecified
metadata.definition: Inflammatory, degenerative, and other disorders of the central and peripheral nervous system without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Inflammatory diseases of the central nervous system
metadata.definition: Inflammatory diseases or disorders of the nerves and ganglia of the brain and spinal cord.
metadata.includes: Meningitis and encephalitis due to prolonged exposure to toxic chemicals; intracranial and intraspinal abscess; phlebitis and thrombophlebitis of intracranial or intraspinal venous sinuses
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries or disorders affecting the central nervous system (11), traumatic intracranial injuries (16), viral encephalitis (3229), viral meningitis

metadata.title: Degenerative diseases of the central nervous system
metadata.definition: Degenerative diseases of the central nervous system.
metadata.includes: Cerebellar ataxia, other spinocerebellar disease, vascular myelopathies, and other myelopathies of the spinal cord; Reye's syndrome; Parkinson's disease; spinocerebellar disease; anterior horn cell disease; encephalopathy; Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis (ALS)
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries or disorders affecting the central nervous system (11); traumatic intracranial injuries (16)

metadata.title: Other disorders of the central nervous system
metadata.definition: Demyelinating diseases and paralytic syndromes of the central nervous system.
metadata.includes: Multiple sclerosis; paralytic syndromes without additional information; nontraumatic herniated brain; anoxic brain damage unless from a traumatic incident
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries or disorders affecting the central nervous system (11); traumatic intracranial injuries (16); seizure disorders resulting from traumatic head injury (16)

metadata.title: Other disorders of the central nervous system— unspecified
metadata.definition: Demyelinating diseases and paralytic syndromes of the central nervous system without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Seizures, seizure disorder
metadata.includes: Epilepsy

metadata.title: Other disorders of the central nervous system— n.e.c.
metadata.includes: Multiple sclerosis; paralytic syndromes without additional information; nontraumatic herniated brain; anoxic brain damage unless from a traumatic incident

metadata.title: Disorders of the peripheral nervous system
metadata.definition: Disorders of the peripheral nervous system which includes the nerves and ganglia located outside the brain and spinal cord. These disorders are also known as neuropathies.
metadata.includes: Mononeuritis of the extremities due to disease; muscular dystrophies; Bell's palsy
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injury affecting the peripheral nervous system (14); carpal tunnel syndrome(27); tarsal tunnel syndrome(27); unspecified repetitive motion disorders (27)

metadata.title: Disorders of the peripheral nervous system— unspecified
metadata.definition: Disorders of the peripheral nervous system without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Inflammatory and toxic neuropathy, toxic polyneuropathy
Disorders of the peripheral nervous system— n.e.c.
metadata.includes: Mononeuritis of the extremities not due to disease; muscular dystrophies; Bell's palsy; paralytic syndromes without additional information; nontraumatic herniated brain; embouchure dystonia; focal dystonia

metadata.title: Disorders of the eye, adnexa, vision
metadata.includes: Disorders of the globe of the eye; nontraumatic retinal detachments; chorioretinal inflammations; disorders of choroid; disorders of the iris and ciliary body; glaucoma; cataracts; nontraumatic visual disturbances; keratitis; disorders of the eyelids, lacrimal system, and other parts of the eye; non-viral, nonspecific acute conjunctivitis; nontraumatic loss of vision; redness of the eye; styes; corneal ulcer;  solar retinopathy; burning sensation in eye not due to trauma or exposure
metadata.excludes: Traumatic injuries occurring to the eye and adnexa of the eye (112); chemical burns to the eye (151); viral conjunctivitis (3261); eye strain, not work related (5123); burns resulting from exposure to ultraviolet light (159); ultraviolet keratoconjunctivitis (1591); welder’s flash, first degree or degree unspecified (1591); chemical conjunctivitis (15); eye injuries resulting from lasers (1129); traumatic loss of vision (112)

metadata.title: Disorders of the eye, adnexa, vision— unspecified
metadata.definition: Disorders of the eye, adnexa, and vision without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Inflammation except conjunctivitis— including ophthalmia, iritis, chalazion
metadata.includes: Chorioretinal inflammations, keratitis ; non-viral, nonspecific, acute conjunctivitis
metadata.excludes: Chemical conjunctivitis (16); viral conjunctivitis (3)

metadata.title: Cataracts
metadata.includes: Corneal ulcer, cataracts

metadata.title: Blindness, low vision, except traumatic
metadata.includes: Nontraumatic loss of vision
metadata.excludes: Traumatic loss of vision due to intracranial injuries (11), loss of eye (12) or injuries to the eye (131)

metadata.title: Glaucoma
metadata.includes: Glaucoma

metadata.title: Visual disturbances
metadata.includes: Nontraumatic visual disturbances, except those due to another condition or disease
metadata.excludes: Traumatic visual disturbances (112)

metadata.title: Disorders of the eye, adnexa, vision— n.e.c.
metadata.includes: Nontraumatic retinal detachments; disorders of choroid; disorders of the eyelids, lacrimal system, and other parts of the eye; styes; solar retinopathy; burning sensation in eye; disorders of the iris and ciliary body

metadata.title: Disorders of the ear, mastoid process, hearing
metadata.definition: Diseases and disorders of the external, middle and inner ear; disorders of tympanic membrane; disorders of the vestibular system; Eustachian tube disorders, and of the mastoid process.
metadata.includes: Mastoiditis, otitis externa, otitis media, otosclerosis, hearing loss sustained from sudden or repeated noise, traumatic and nontraumatic hearing loss, otalgia
metadata.excludes: Aero-otitis media (1731), barotitis (1731), otitic barotrauma (1731), ruptured eardrum due to air or water pressure (136), earache without further description (5122)

metadata.title: Disorders of the ear, mastoid process, hearing— unspecified
metadata.definition: Disorders of the ear, mastoid process, hearing without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Deafness, hearing loss and impairment
metadata.includes: Hearing loss sustained from sudden or repeated noise; traumatic and nontraumatic hearing loss

metadata.title: Tinnitus
metadata.includes: Ringing of the ears

metadata.title: Disorders of the ear, mastoid process, and hearing— n.e.c.
metadata.includes: Mastoiditis, otitis externa, otosclerosis, otalgia

metadata.title: Nervous system and sense organs diseases— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Diseases of the nervous system and sense organs that are not classified by any other code within major group 22.
metadata.includes: Anosmia or loss of sense of smell

metadata.title: Circulatory system diseases
metadata.definition: Diseases or disorders affecting the heart and vascular system.
metadata.includes: Heart attack; chronic rheumatic heart disease and acute rheumatic fever; hypertensive heart disease; ischemic heart disease; diseases of pulmonary circulation; cerebrovascular disease; diseases of arteries, arterioles, and capillaries; diseases of veins and lymphatics ; other diseases of the circulatory system; blood clots that are nontraumatic in nature and that are not specified as being in either an artery or a vein; nontraumatic rupture of blood vessels

metadata.title: Circulatory system diseases— unspecified
metadata.definition: Diseases or disorders affecting the heart and vascular system without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Rheumatic fever with heart involvement
metadata.includes: Chronic rheumatic heart disease, rheumatic carditis,

metadata.title: Hypertensive disease
metadata.definition: Essential hypertension; hypertensive heart disease; and hypertensive renal disease.

metadata.title: Ischemic heart disease— unspecified

metadata.title: Angina

metadata.title: Ischemic heart disease— n.e.c.

metadata.title: Diseases of pulmonary circulation

metadata.title: Diseases of pulmonary circulation— unspecified
metadata.definition: Acute and chronic pulmonary heart disease, and other diseases of pulmonary circulation without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Diseases of pulmonary circulation— n.e.c.

metadata.title: Other forms of heart disease
metadata.definition: Heart disease that is not classified in any other nature group in major group 23.

metadata.title: Other forms of heart disease— unspecified
metadata.definition: Other forms of heart disease without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Toxic myocarditis
metadata.includes: Toxic acute myocarditis

Other forms of heart disease— n.e.c.

metadata.title: Cerebrovascular disease

metadata.title: Cerebrovascular disease— unspecified
metadata.definition: Subarachnoid, intracerebral, and other unspecified intracranial hemorrhage that are not associated with a traumatic event without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: Diseases of arteries, arterioles, capillaries

metadata.excludes: Traumatic internal injuries to organs and blood vessels of the trunk (123); traumatic intracranial injuries (111); traumatic bruises and contusions (134); nontraumatic aneurysm of pulmonary artery (2349); pulmonary embolism (2342); embolisms resulting from diving (1733); venous embolisms (2389); stroke (2361)

metadata.title: Diseases of arteries, arterioles, capillaries— unspecified
metadata.definition: Diseases peculiar to arteries, arterioles, and capillaries without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.excludes: Traumatic internal injuries to organs and blood vessels of the trunk (123); traumatic bruises and contusions (134); traumatic intracranial injuries (111); pulmonary embolism (2342); embolisms resulting from diving (1733); arterial embolisms (2379)

metadata.definition: Diseases of the veins and lymphatics without enough information to further classify the condition into any of the detailed subcategories.

metadata.title: INFECTIOUS AND PARASITIC DISEASES
metadata.definition: Nature Division 3 classifies five types of infections: bacterial, viral, rickettsial, fungal, and parasitic infections. These infectious agents are transmitted to a person through inhalation, ingestion, or contact with the skin. These diseases are generally recognized as communicable or transmissible, with a few of unknown but possibly infectious origin.
metadata.includes: Bacterial diseases; viral diseases; Other non-viral arthropod-borne diseases; Mycoses (fungal infections); Helminthiases (worm infections); Infectious diseases peculiar to the intestines; Other infectious and parasitic diseases

metadata.title: NEOPLASMS, TUMORS, AND CANCERS
metadata.definition: Nature Division 4 classifies diseases or conditions related to tumors, or neoplasms: the new growth of tissue in which the multiplication of cells is uncontrolled and progressive. The behavior of tumors or neoplasms may be benign, cancerous, or of uncertain behavior at the time of diagnosis.

metadata.title: Malignant neoplasms and tumors (cancers, carcinomas, sarcomas)
metadata.definition: Nature group 41 classifies cancers. Categories are grouped by location or site.  In general, the site of the original malignant neoplasm should govern the code that is assigned. Malignant neoplasms, or tumors, are divided into two broad categories of carcinoma and sarcoma; both are included in this major group.

metadata.title: SYMPTOMS, SIGNS, AND ILL-DEFINED CONDITIONS
metadata.definition: Nature Division 5 classifies those ill-defined conditions that cannot be classified elsewhere. These may manifest as symptoms, signs, or abnormal results from laboratory or investigative medical tests or procedures. Codes from this division should be used when no specific diagnosis is named and cannot be inferred from information found on the source document. Signs and symptoms coded here may be related to an occupational illness or a non-work related condition, but symptoms of traumatic work injuries or overexertion are excluded.
metadata.includes: Sick building syndrome; eye strain
metadata.excludes: Unspecified or nonspecific injuries resulting from traumatic incidents or exposures (10)

metadata.title: Symptoms, signs, and ill-defined conditions— unspecified
Symptoms

metadata.includes: Sick building syndrome with unspecified symptoms

metadata.title: Mental disorders and syndromes
metadata.definition: Nature group 62 includes neurotic, psychotic and organic mental disorders or syndromes resulting from underlying physical conditions of the worker or repetitive or ongoing conditions of the work environment. When mental disorders or syndromes are described as sequelae or aftereffect of a traumatic injury or disorder, the initial or underlying condition should be coded. For example, if the individual is experiencing acute depression as a result of chronic pain from a back injury, code the back injury. Mental trauma that does not develop into a disorder resulting from a single incident should be coded in Division 1.
metadata.excludes: Acute incidences of stress resulting from a single stressful event

metadata.title: Mental disorders and syndromes— unspecified
metadata.definition: Nature 620 classifies instances where mental disorders or syndromes are specified without

metadata.title: Anxiety, stress— unspecified
metadata.definition: Stress or anxiety of unspecified duration.
metadata.includes: Job-related stress, unspecified; mental anguish or stress

metadata.title: Post-traumatic stress disorder
metadata.definition: A disorder in which a person experiences longer term physical and emotional symptoms following a traumatic event. Select this code if case information documents this condition
metadata.includes: Ongoing nightmares; intrusive thoughts; heightened reactions, depression
metadata.excludes: Short term stress reaction to trauma immediately following incident, traumatic shock (191)

metadata.title: Anxiety or panic— multiple episodes
metadata.definition: Ongoing or recurring stress, anxiety or panic attacks.
metadata.includes: Situational depression; adjustment disorder; panic or anxiety disorders

metadata.title: Anxiety or panic attack— single episode
metadata.definition: Short-term or single episodes of anxiety, panic, or stress following an traumatic event or exposure.
metadata.includes: Anxiety concerning exposure to a disease, such as HIV;

metadata.title: Mental disorders and syndromes— n.e.c.
metadata.definition: Nature code 629 classifies other mental disorders or syndromes not classified elsewhere.
metadata.includes: Substance-induced mental disorder.

metadata.title: Other diseases, conditions, and disorders— n.e.c.
EXPOSURES TO HARMFUL SUBSTANCE OR ENVIRONMENT—NO INJURY OR ILLNESS INCURRED
metadata.definition: Nature Division 7 classifies instances in which the worker was exposed to a disease, but did not come down with the illness or exhibit any symptoms. For example, this code would be selected if there was an exposure to tuberculosis, but TB test results were negative.  If a worker contracted a disease from a needlestick, code the disease (Nature 3). If the needle was known to be contaminated, code the exposure (Nature 7). If the needle was not known to be contaminated (Nature 132)
metadata.includes: Bloodborne pathogen exposure (BBP); bodily fluid exposure; needlestick injury without contracting disease

metadata.title: MULTIPLE DISEASES, CONDITIONS, AND DISORDERS
metadata.definition: Nature Division 8 classifies multiple physical characteristics whose individual codes are found in two or more of the following divisions: Diseases and Disorders of Body Systems; Infectious and Parasitic Diseases; Neoplasms, Tumors, and Cancers; Symptoms, Signs, and Ill-defined Conditions; and Other Diseases, Conditions, and Disorders. The conditions classified in this Division should not be an injury and its sequela (i.e. a wound that becomes infected), but should be used when two distinct natures spanning divisions are transmitted in the same event.
metadata.excludes: Multiple traumatic injuries and disorders are coded in 18.

metadata.title: Traumatic injuries and mental disorders
metadata.definition: Nature group 81 includes severe and disabling traumatic injuries with equally debilitating diagnosed mental disorders. In this group, mental disorders are treated as distinct injuries and not sequelae of another traumatic injury to the physical body.

metadata.title: Gunshot wounds and PTSD
metadata.definition: Nature code 812 may be used when PTSD results from an assault or confrontation with another person and results in gunshot wounds or when a person suffering from PTSD injures himself/herself with a gun.

metadata.title: Trauma involving internal organs and major blood vessels and PTSD
Third degree or higher burns and PTSD
Traumatic injuries and damage to prosthetic or orthopedic devices
Traumatic injuries and infectious disease
metadata.definition: Nature code 830 may be used when an infectious disease is transmitted at the same time as a severe wound or trauma. For example, if a person is assaulted and receives severe physical injuries as well as transmission of a blood-borne pathogen.
metadata.includes: Infectious disease AND traumatic injuries from the following Groups: 11, 12, or third degree or higher burns 15
metadata.excludes: Sequela infection of an open wound

metadata.title: Nature— unspecified
metadata.definition: Nature code 990 classifies cases where there is insufficient information to select even an unspecified code at the division level.
